An algorithm to build suffix array and BWT by the external induced sorting method.
====================================================================================


Description
-----------

This package implements suffix array and BWT construction algorithms for massive datasets using the external induced sorting method. It is mainly used to verify these algorithms and evaluate their performance.


Requirements
------------
The 'icpc' compiler within Intel oneAPI is required, with no other external dependencies.


Compilation and usage
---------------------
Type 'make' to build the executable file called 'build_bwt' to build suffix array and/or BWT. The output suffix array and BWT will be written to sample.txt.sa5 and sample.txt.bwt, and each element of suffix array and BWT is encoded by 5 and 1 byte, respectively. By default, the algorithm uses 24 GiB of RAM, 2 MiB I/O buffer, and 200 MiB file blocks.

There are three cases to build SA or BWT as follows:

1. To build BWT only, run the command of './build_bwt sample.txt -bwt';

2. To build SA only, run the command of './build_bwt sample.txt -sa';

3. To build BWT and SA, run the command of './build_bwt sample.txt -bwtsa';



Limitations
------------
- The current implementation version uses 24 GiB of RAM by default.
- The input can not contain the character 0. If it contains the character of 0, compile './tool/format.cpp' to generate a format tool named 'format', execute the command './format sample.txt' to produce the formated file 'sample.txt.format', and finally execute the command './build_sa_bwt sample.txt.format' to build its suffix array and BWT.


Troubleshooting
---------------

- If the program throws the error '_file is nullptr' and pauses, the limit of the maximum number of files opened by a program is broken. A solution is to use the "ulimit -n newlimit" command to increase this file limit. For example, increase this maximum number with 'ulimit -n 102400' command.

- If there are some temporary files in the input directory named 'tmp_file_*', please delete them directly.


Tools
--------------
- './tool/skyline.cpp' is a tool to generate the dataset of skyline.
- './tool/format.cpp' is to format the alphabet of an input with non-zero characters.


